, 7, 10, 14, 18, 21, 74], [16, 20, 22, 24, 25, 32, 33], [15, 16, 17, 19, 20], [0, 4, 6, 7, 8, 11], [13, 19, 20, 21, 69, 78], [10, 12, 13, 17, 20, 22], [10, 13, 16, 18, 19], [10, 11, 17, 19, 21], [13, 15, 17, 18, 21], [12, 13, 15, 16, 24, 67, 78], [11, 15, 18, 19, 69, 74], [10, 12, 16, 32], [24, 27, 29, 30, 33, 71], [12, 20, 23, 33, 67, 71], [12, 30, 31, 32, 33], [27, 28, 48, 50, 57], [23, 26, 28, 30, 71], [26, 27, 30, 32, 53, 57], [23, 30, 31, 33], [23, 25, 27, 28, 29, 31, 32], [25, 29, 30, 33], [10, 12, 22, 25, 28, 30, 53], [12, 23, 24, 25, 29, 31], [38, 41, 43, 46, 55], [3, 10, 37, 44, 47, 52, 53], [37, 42, 59, 65], [35, 36, 42, 44, 52, 59], [34, 41, 45, 55], [48, 49, 50, 58, 61, 62], [51, 58, 60, 62, 66, 68], [34, 38, 43, 63], [36, 37, 44, 46, 65], [34, 41, 44, 46, 63], [1, 3, 9, 35, 37, 42, 43, 46, 63], [38, 54, 55, 56, 60], [34, 42, 43, 44, 55, 56, 64, 65], [35, 49, 52, 53, 57, 58, 59, 61], [26, 39, 50, 62, 66], [39, 47, 58, 61], [26, 39, 48, 57, 61], [40, 56, 58, 60], [35, 37, 47, 59], [10, 28, 32, 35, 47, 57], [45, 55, 56, 64], [34, 38, 45, 46, 54, 64], [45, 46, 51, 54, 58, 59, 60, 64, 65], [26, 28, 47, 50, 53, 61], [39, 40, 47, 49, 51, 56, 59, 62], [36, 37, 47, 52, 56, 58, 65], [40, 45, 51, 56], [39, 47, 49, 50, 57], [39, 40, 48, 58, 66], [1, 41, 43, 44, 73], [46, 54, 55, 56], [36, 42, 46, 56, 59], [40, 48, 62, 68], [20, 24, 71, 72], [40, 66], [15, 21, 74, 76, 78], [4, 5, 75, 77, 79], [23, 24, 27, 67, 72], [67, 71], [1, 2, 63], [4, 11, 21, 69, 76], [4, 70, 76, 79], [4, 69, 74, 75, 78], [2, 5, 70], [15, 20, 69, 76], [70, 75]], \"note\": \"neighbors[i] is the list of precinct indices that share a boundary with precinct i (4-connected on the rasterized Voronoi map). Use this to compute connected components on an opened site's assigned-precinct subgraph: more than one component means a non-contiguous service area.\"}"}, {"content": "{\"split_sites\":[{\"index\":4,\"reason\":\"Two components: {0,4,8,14} and isolated {74}; precinct 74 only touches 11,21,69,76, all