cinct indices that share a boundary with precinct i (4-connected on the rasterized Voronoi map). Use this to compute connected components on an opened site's assigned-precinct subgraph: more than one component means a non-contiguous service area.\"}"}, {"content": "{\"split_sites\":[{\"index\":4,\"reason\":\"Two components: {2,4,7,10,76} and isolated {70}; no adjacency from 70 to other site-4 precincts.\"},{\"index\":8,\"reason\":\"Two components: {3,8,11,14,17,20} and isolated {15}; precinct 15 only touches non-site-8 neighbors.\"},{\"index\":23,\"reason\":\"Two components: {34,42,50,53,55,61,64,65} and isolated {58}; precinct 58 connects only to non-site-23 precincts.\"},{\"index\":30,\"reason\":\"Two components: {36,48,54,57,60,62,69} and isolated {52}; precinct 52 has no adjacent precinct assigned to site 30.\"},{\"index\":39,\"reason\":\"Two components: {33,75,79} and isolated {78}; precinct 78 is adjacent only to precincts 67 and 79, with 79 in the other component.\"}]}", "role": "assistant", "annotations": []}]}}
