[25, 26, 28, 33], [23, 26, 27, 30, 33], [23, 31, 71, 77], [19, 23, 24, 28, 33], [23, 26, 29, 66, 77], [12, 16, 17, 19, 25, 33], [19, 25, 27, 28, 30, 32], [26, 41, 55, 59, 66], [57, 58], [37, 38, 49, 53, 62], [5, 36, 44, 47, 53, 56, 62], [36, 49, 53, 61, 65], [40, 43, 50, 54, 63], [39, 50, 54, 61], [25, 26, 34, 45, 52, 59], [43, 57, 60, 63, 64], [39, 42, 50, 57, 58, 63], [37, 46, 53, 56, 65], [41, 46, 48, 52, 56, 59, 63, 64], [44, 45, 48, 56, 65], [5, 37, 51, 62, 76, 78], [45, 46, 61, 63, 65], [36, 38, 62, 73], [39, 40, 43], [47, 62, 73, 78], [12, 25, 41, 45, 56], [36, 37, 38, 44, 65], [39, 40, 61, 63], [34, 59, 60, 66], [0, 5, 6, 12, 37, 44, 45, 46, 52], [35, 42, 43, 58, 60], [35, 43, 57], [34, 41, 45, 55, 60, 64], [42, 55, 57, 59, 64, 66], [38, 40, 48, 54, 63, 65], [36, 37, 47, 49, 51, 73], [39, 42, 43, 45, 48, 54, 61, 64], [42, 45, 59, 60, 63], [38, 44, 46, 48, 53, 61], [26, 31, 34, 55, 60, 77], [24, 70, 71, 79], [1, 74, 76], [72, 74, 75], [67, 71], [23, 24, 29, 67, 70, 77], [1, 7, 10, 11, 15, 69, 74], [49, 51, 62, 78], [1, 68, 69, 72, 75], [69, 74], [1, 5, 9, 47, 68], [29, 31, 66, 71], [47, 51, 73], [19, 24, 67]], \"note\": \"neighbors[i] is the list of precinct indices that share a boundary with precinct i (4-connected on the rasterized Voronoi map). Use this to compute connected components on an opened site's assigned-precinct subgraph: more than one component means a non-contiguous service area.\"}"}, {"content": "{\"split_sites\":[{\"index\":21,\"reason\":\"Purple site 21 appears in two NW patches: mid-left around (1.2,6.5)-(2.6,7.8) and upper-left around (3.4,9.3); adjacency/assignments split {36,38,49,51,53,62,73} into two components.\"},{\"index\":23,\"reason\":\"Lavender site 23 shows a north-central block around (5.4-7.4,6.9-9.5) plus a separate small east patch near (8.2,6.3); adjacency confirms precinct 42 isolated from others assigned to 23.\"},{\"index\":33,\"reason\":\"Olive site 33 has a large west-central area near (0.3-2.3,4.8-6.0) and a detached