{"row_id": 53, "pair_id": "contiguity_med_17", "archetype": "contiguity", "difficulty": "med", "task": "identify", "renderer": "v2_no_markers", "prompt": "multimodal_full", "model": "openai_vlm_tools:gpt-5.4", "raw_response": "{\"split_sites\":[{\"index\":3,\"reason\":\"Orange area splits into central-south patch and isolated east-edge patch near (7.1,3.6); assignments show precincts 13,14,15,17,18,19,20,21,27,28,29 to site 3, with precinct 29 disconnected in adjacency.\"},{\"index\":5,\"reason\":\"Peach area appears in west-middle and small southwest-central patch near (0.9,2.9), separated by blue; assignments 9,68,75,79 to site 5, and precinct 79 is disconnected from 9/68/75 in adjacency.\"},{\"index\":17,\"reason\":\"Purple area splits into main northwest block and tiny far-northwest corner near (0.7,9.4); site 17 serves precincts 36,39,40,45,62,77, and precinct 77 is adjacency-isolated from the others.\"},{\"index\":25,\"reason\":\"Pink area has a mid-east band around (8.0,5.1) and a separate tiny patch near (7.6,7.2); site 25 serves precincts 25 and 38 only, which are non-adjacent.\"},{\"index\":29,\"reason\":\"Gray area splits into broad west-central block and small strip near (0.6,5.7), separated by peach; site 29 serves 48,53,54,57,59,64,78, and precinct 78 is disconnected in adjacency.\"}]}", "parsed_answer": {"split_sites": [3, 5, 17, 25, 29], "reasons": {"3": "Orange area splits into central-south patch and isolated east-edge patch near (7.1,3.6); assignments show precincts 13,14,15,17,18,19,20,21,27,28,29 to site 3, with precinct 29 disconnected in adjacency.", "5": "Peach area appears in west-middle and small southwest-central patch near (0.9,2.9), separated by blue; assignments 9,68,75,79 to site 5, and precinct 79 is disconnected from 9/68/75 in adjacency.", "17": "Purple area splits into main northwest block and tiny far-northwest corner near (0.7,9.4); site 17 serves precincts 36,39,40,45,62,77, and precinct 77 is adjacency-isolated from the others.", "25": "Pink area has a mid-east band around (8.0,5.1) and a separate tiny patch near (7.6,7.2); site 25 serves precincts 25 and 38 only, which are non-adjacent.", "29": "Gray area splits into broad west-central block and small strip near (0.6,5.7), separated by peach; site 29 serves 48,53,54,57,59,64,78, and precinct 78 is disconnected in adjacency."}}, "score": 0.33333333333333337, "secondary_scores": {"pred_size": 5.0, "truth_size": 1.0, "fp_count": 4.0, "fn_count": 0.0, "tp_count": 1.0, "precision": 0.2, "recall": 1.0}, "tool_calls": 3, "tool_call_log": [{"name": "list_sites", "arguments": "{\"opened_only\": true}", "result_preview": "[{\"index\": 1, \"x\": 2.1802227977195687, \"y\": 2.171721554276343, \"type\": \"school\", \"capacity\": 5000, \"opened\": true, \"load\": 2729}, {\"index\": 2, \"x\": 3.367674456879912, \"y\": 4.0051078202754, \"type\": \"co"}, {"name": "get_current_assignments", "arguments": "{}", "result_preview": "{\"n_precincts\": 80, \"n_returned\": 80, \"assignments\": [{\"precinct\": 0, \"x\": 4.019405784683789, \"y\": 2.675589931222931, \"voters\": 531, \"assigned_site\": 7, \"assigned_distance\": 1.2571174097496776, \"weigh"}, {"name": "get_precinct_adjacency", "arguments": "{}", "result_preview": "{\"n_precincts\": 80, \"neighbors\": [[3, 4, 11, 12, 17, 22], [2, 5, 9, 10, 79], [1, 8, 10, 67, 76, 79], [0, 7, 9, 12, 22], [0, 6, 9, 11, 12], [1, 6, 9, 10], [4, 5, 8, 9, 10, 11], [3, 9, 22, 37, 54, 75], "}], "elapsed_sec": 10.296433925628662, "error": "", "api_metadata": {"usage": {"completion_tokens": 385, "prompt_tokens": 16307, "total_tokens": 16692, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": 0, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 0, "rejected_prediction_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 2432}}, "finish_reason": "stop", "model_resolved": "gpt-5.4-2026-03-05", "system_fingerprint": null, "request_id": "chatcmpl-Ddfo0kZU3tUpU43Yhlm59HUWZA6Z6", "n_turns": 2, "per_turn_finish_reasons": ["tool_calls", "stop"], "conversation": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are a careful analyst examining a map of a polling-place plan, with full structured-tool access alongside the map.\n\nOn the map: each precinct is filled with the color of its assigned opened polling place, designating a catchment area. Polling-place locations themselves are NOT drawn on the map \u2014 the only visible signal is the colored fill.\n\nYou also have access to the following structured tools:\n  list_sites(opened_only) \u2014 candidate or opened polling places (index, location in km, capacity, type, opened/closed status, current voter load if opened).\n  get_precinct_centroids(precinct_indices) \u2014 centroid coordinates in km of the requested precincts (omit `precinct_indices` for all precincts).\n  get_precinct_adjacency() \u2014 for each precinct, the indices of its spatially-adjacent precincts (4-connected on the rasterised Voronoi map). Useful for connectivity questions.\n  get_current_assignments(precinct_indices) \u2014 for each precinct, the polling place it is currently assigned to and the assigned travel distance. Omit `precinct_indices` for all.\n  get_assigned_site_at(x, y) \u2014 the polling place currently serving the precinct that contains coordinate (x, y).\n\nUse BOTH channels as appropriate to the question:\n  - The MAP is best for spatial PATTERNS \u2014 clusters, irregular catchment shapes, large under-served regions, obviously-disjoint same-color patches. Visual scans surface anomalies that would be expensive to enumerate via tools.\n  - The structured TOOLS are best for PRECISE values \u2014 exact distances, specific assigned-site indices, connectivity verification, candidate enumeration. Tools are exact; the map is approximate.\n\nCommon workflow: scan the map visually to localise the issue, then call structured tools to confirm specific entities and values. The map is roughly 0\u201310 km on each axis, with about 80 precincts and 18 opened polling places. When you have enough information, respond in the format the user requests."}, {"role": "user", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The map shows a polling-place plan for a county. Each precinct is filled with the color of its assigned opened polling place. Polling-place locations themselves are NOT drawn on the map \u2014 the only visible signal is the colored service-area fill.\n\nA polling place's *service area* is the set of precincts assigned to it \u2014 i.e. all precincts sharing its color on the map.\n\nA service area is **non-contiguous** when its precincts form two or more visually disjoint patches on the map (the same color appears in separated pieces, with other colors between them).\n\nFor every opened polling place whose service area is non-contiguous, report it together with a brief reason explaining the evidence. If every service area is contiguous, return an empty list.\n\nRespond with ONLY a JSON object of the form:\n  {\"split_sites\": [\n    {\"index\": <i>, \"reason\": \"<short justification>\"},\n    ...\n  ]}\nEach `reason` should briefly state which colored regions you saw, roughly where on the map, and (if you used the tool) which coordinates / tool calls confirmed the split. Keep each reason under 40 words. Do not include any other text outside the JSON."}, {"type": "image_url", "image_url": {"url": "<image: 88626 chars>"}}]}, {"role": "assistant", "annotations": [], "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_Nz0ykp4GdEMbr2wwOCjge6jc", "function": {"arguments": "{\"opened_only\": true}", "name": "list_sites"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_twTp3plo64sEBZjcaDpx4Bah", "function": {"arguments": "{}", "name": "get_current_assignments"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_fi08Vj5nw8ajYQkeZq3PbQE4", "function": {"arguments": "{}", "name": "get_precinct_adjacency"}, "type": "function"}]}, {"role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_Nz0ykp4GdEMbr2wwOCjge6jc", "content": "[{\"index\": 1, \"x\": 2.1802227977195687, \"y\": 2.171721554276343, \"type\": \"school\"