ing your final answer. When you have enough information, respond in the format requested by the user."}, {"role": "user", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The map shows a polling-place plan for a county. Each precinct is filled with the color of its assigned opened polling place. Polling-place locations themselves are NOT drawn on the map \u2014 the only visible signal is the colored service-area fill.\n\nA polling place's *service area* is the set of precincts assigned to it \u2014 i.e. all precincts sharing its color on the map.\n\nA service area is **non-contiguous** when its precincts form two or more visually disjoint patches on the map (the same color appears in separated pieces, with other colors between them).\n\nFor every opened polling place whose service area is non-contiguous, report it together with a brief reason explaining the evidence. If every service area is contiguous, return an empty list.\n\nRespond with ONLY a JSON object of the form:\n  {\"split_sites\": [\n    {\"index\": <i>, \"reason\": \"<short justification>\"},\n    ...\n  ]}\nEach `reason` should briefly state which colored regions you saw, roughly where on the map, and (if you used the tool) which coordinates / tool calls confirmed the split. Keep each reason under 40 words. Do not include any other text outside the JSON."}, {"type": "image_url", "image_url": {"url": "<image: 96694 chars>"}}]}, {"role": "assistant", "annotations": [], "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_N6Gjsi8ynOeWp7iTqhMSIglJ", "function": {"arguments": "{\"x\": 8.7, \"y\": 2.0}", "name": "get_assigned_site_at"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_nvoMA4PJMn5rPbFbstMemj87", "function": {"arguments": "{\"x\": 1.1, \"y\": 1.0}", "name": "get_assigned_site_at"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_ACeiU9dPjtgPcf7uIXA7Wz08", "function": {"arguments": "{\"x\": 8.9, \"y\": 8.9}", "name": "get_assigned_site_at"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_PAGxEVjVZHsmfZ2ryOWkcfER", "function": {"arguments": "{\"x\": 7.0, \"y\": 7.0}", "na