16, 23, 24, 29, 31], [27, 30, 32, 33, 45, 66], [26, 29, 30, 33], [66, 70, 72], [23, 25, 27, 30, 31, 33, 46], [26, 27, 29, 40, 45, 46, 58], [16, 18, 20, 25, 29, 46, 50], [23, 26, 33, 66, 72], [23, 26, 27, 29, 32], [38, 41, 42, 49], [41, 48, 52, 54, 55, 63], [40, 43, 51, 56, 58, 59, 61], [40, 45, 51, 56, 76], [34, 41, 47, 55], [4, 52, 63, 67, 68], [30, 36, 37, 45, 56, 58], [34, 35, 38, 42, 48, 55], [34, 41, 48, 49, 57], [36, 59, 60, 61], [47, 60, 61, 62], [26, 30, 37, 40, 76], [29, 30, 31, 50, 58, 59], [38, 44, 55, 60, 64], [35, 41, 42, 52, 57], [34, 42, 57, 68], [5, 11, 18, 31, 46, 53, 59, 63, 65], [36, 37, 56, 61, 76], [35, 39, 48, 57, 63, 68], [50, 54, 63, 65], [35, 53, 55, 63, 65], [35, 38, 41, 47, 54, 64, 65], [36, 37, 40, 51], [42, 48, 49, 52, 68], [30, 36, 40, 46, 59], [36, 43, 46, 50, 58, 60, 65], [43, 44, 47, 59, 61, 64, 65], [36, 43, 44, 51, 60, 62, 76], [44, 61, 76], [0, 4, 11, 35, 39, 50, 52, 53, 54], [47, 55, 60, 65], [50, 53, 54, 55, 59, 60, 64], [26, 28, 32, 72], [2, 4, 6, 39, 78], [39, 49, 52, 57], [3, 8, 10, 14, 15, 17, 22, 74, 79], [28, 71, 72], [12, 70, 72, 79], [12, 24, 28, 32, 66, 70, 71], [3, 74, 75, 77], [3, 69, 73, 77], [2, 3, 73, 77], [37, 45, 51, 61, 62], [2, 73, 74, 75], [1, 2, 6, 67], [12, 15, 20, 69, 71]], \"note\": \"neighbors[i] is the list of precinct indices that share a boundary with precinct i (4-connected on the rasterized Voronoi map). Use this to compute connected components on an opened site's assigned-precinct subgraph: more than one component means a non-contiguous service area.\"}"}, {"content": "{\"split_sites\":[{\"index\":2,\"reason\":\"Orange area splits into southwest block and small central patch near (2.6,4.3); adjacency on assigned precincts {0,1,3,8,9,10,73,74} vs isolated {31} confirms two components.\"},{\"index\":28,\"reason\":\"Tan area splits into northwest corner near (0.7,9.2) and separate west-mid patch near (0.5,7.6); assigned precincts {34,49,57} and isolated {68} are disconnected in adjacency.\"},{\"index\"